1
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:12,880
(Previously)
Grandma!

2
00:00:12,881 --> 00:00:14,519
What if something happens to her?

3
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:16,160
Your grandma is going to be okay.

4
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,920
Can you forgive me?

5
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:21,479
But there is something...

6
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:23,440
I need you to help me with.

7
00:00:23,840 --> 00:00:26,120
You've become much cuter than before.

8
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:28,080
Come and give Daddy a hug.

9
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:38,240
Come with me, okay?

10
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:47,900
"Love Like a Bike"
(Episode 6)

11
00:01:50,320 --> 00:01:52,720
Hey. Hey.

12
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:55,160
Boyfriend.

13
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:57,680
Oh...

14
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,160
Look who's here.

15
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:00,920
How did you know I was here?

16
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,680
Dindin told me.

17
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,680
Come on, let's go home.

18
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:07,480
Can you walk?

19
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:11,680
Careful now.

20
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:17,560
Nava? What's wrong?

21
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,800
Nava. Nava.

22
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,600
My stomach hurts.

23
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:38,400
(Several months earlier)

24
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:51,000
Hey there.

25
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,760
How's it going?

26
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,200
Let me see.

27
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:02,360
This is amazing.

28
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:04,040
Gorgeous.

29
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:07,120
Did you know that client loves your work?

30
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,680
You're gonna make us rich.

31
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:11,960
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Keep it up.

32
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,400
Go for it.

33
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:27,719
The 15-second board is roughly like this.

34
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:30,440
And the KV really fits

35
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:33,120
the 'Future of Pattaya' theme.

36
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:38,800
This isn't what I had in mind at all.

37
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:41,359
And isn't this KV too cluttered?

38
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:43,279
- But—
- Can you clean it up a bit?

39
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:45,519
But these are what you chose...

40
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:49,040
It doesn't look good now. Just fix it.

41
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,240
Yes.

42
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:55,999
Go. Hurry up and fix it.

43
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:59,920
Don't worry, he'll be done in 30 minutes.

44
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:02,800
Let's move on to the wardrobe.

45
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:05,120
Relax, have some water first.

46
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:11,040
Chai, put some more light in the back.

47
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:20,400
Mr. Nava!
Why isn't the model on set yet?!

48
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,360
I'll check right now.

49
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,120
Where is she?

50
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:26,800
She won't come out.

51
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:30,400
- Why won't she come out?
- Says it's too hot. I tried my best.

52
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,400
There are 30 minutes left.

53
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,656
Can you shoot something else for now?

54
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,120
How can I? There's nothing to...

55
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:38,000
- Nava!
- Yes, Ma'am!

56
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:40,520
What are you doing?!
The client is waiting!

57
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:43,239
- Go and get her now.
- Alright, fine.

58
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:45,120
It's boiling out here!

59
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:47,880
Why did you want to shoot under the sun?!

60
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:52,560
Okay, you can pose now.

61
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:56,000
Great. Please change a pose.

62
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,520
Looks good.

63
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,240
Stop! Stop right there!

64
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:01,559
That's the wrong product!

65
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,999
C… Cut.

66
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,400
- Not this one?
- No!

67
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,759
One moment, please.

68
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:10,200
- Please hold this one.
- When will it be over?

69
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,879
- Just a moment, please.
- It's so hot.

70
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,039
Nava!

71
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:16,360
- Yes, Ma'am?
- We're running out of time! And it's hot!

72
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:17,679
Yes! Please bear with me for a moment.

73
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,679
We only have the slot until noon!

74
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:22,680
Please have a look at the monitor.

75
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,440
Wake up!

76
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:38,800
Yes, Ma'am?

77
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:42,360
The deadline is 9 AM!
How can you finish it if you're sleeping?!

78
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,360
Yes, I'll be as quick as possible.

79
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:46,079
Are you sure?

80
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:49,279
If you miss this, the company
is finished because of you.

81
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:50,520
I… I'll get it done.

82
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:52,000
Then hurry up!

83
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:55,200
The deadline's coming
and you're sleeping!

84
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,600
Do I…

85
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,360
have cancer, Doctor?

86
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:37,560
Yes. You are in stage 2.

87
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:41,960
Fortunately, it's still treatable.

88
00:06:43,353 --> 00:06:45,433
If we start the treatment soon,

89
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:48,560
there's a high chance of recovery.

90
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:51,600
Please make an appointment

91
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,520
when you're ready.

92
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:56,080
Nava.

93
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:59,120
You're too sick to work.
Just go get treated.

94
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:00,760
You can't work for me.

95
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:01,800
I can handle it.

96
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,720
Handle what? Look at your condition.

97
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:05,800
I really can.

98
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:09,600
You can't. Besides, I've already
found someone to replace you.

99
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:11,079
I can really do this, please.

100
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:14,160
Just go. I'll pay your severance.

101
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:16,400
Now, everyone, back to work.

102
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,959
Are you a relative of Mr. Nava?

103
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:47,000
Yes, I'm his boyfriend.

104
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,800
What's happening to Nava?

105
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,640
Mr. Nawa has stage 2 cancer.

106
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:59,680
Stage 2… cancer?

107
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:06,720
Yes, we've tried
to contact him for treatment,

108
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:09,320
but he never showed up.

109
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:13,200
The patient's condition
has weakened so much.

110
00:08:13,486 --> 00:08:16,366
We must start treatment immediately

111
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:19,240
before it progresses further.

112
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,240
Nava.

113
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,960
How are you?

114
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:40,160
Please discuss this with him.

115
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:42,479
Yes.

116
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,480
Thank you so much.

117
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:44,760
Please excuse me.

118
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,440
Nava,

119
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:57,800
why did you keep this from me?

120
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,720
Why didn't you tell me?

121
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,400
Because I knew.

122
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:13,200
I knew you'd be devastated.

123
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,720
Let's break up.

124
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,960
Nava…

125
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,280
I'm going to die anyway.

126
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:38,880
Leaving now...

127
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:41,800
or when I'm gone, it's all the same.

128
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,400
No,

129
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:51,080
I'm not breaking up with you.

130
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,680
I'm not going anywhere.

131
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,280
You're going to be okay.

132
00:09:57,240 --> 00:10:00,560
The doctor said it's not terminal yet.

133
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,096
If we start now, there's still a chance...

134
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:03,920
What's the point, Sky?!

135
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,920
It's cancer.

136
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,080
I'm going to die anyway.

137
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,360
Treatment is just more torture.

138
00:10:12,560 --> 00:10:14,160
Don't think like that.

139
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:19,640
The doctor confirmed that there's
still a high chance you'll recover.

140
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:23,320
Enough.

141
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:27,600
It's so unfair.

142
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,440
I lived a good life.

143
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:35,920
I didn't drink, I didn't smoke.

144
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:39,160
I gave everything to my work.

145
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,520
And what did I get?

146
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:47,600
A tumor… and a pink slip.

147
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:52,000
How is that fair?

148
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,920
It's so damn unfair.

149
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,160
It's okay, Nava.

150
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:05,040
It's okay. I'm right here.

151
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:07,480
I'm by your side.

152
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,720
I'll stay here until you're healed.

153
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,360
I promise.

154
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:26,480
Koh Larn, this way please!

155
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:28,120
Thank you.

156
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:31,240
Thank you.

157
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:33,640
Thank you.

158
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,880
Koh Larn, this way!

159
00:11:36,920 --> 00:11:38,840
Thank you, enjoy your trip.

160
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:41,279
Koh Larn, this way! Thank you.

161
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:42,560
Enjoy your trip.

162
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:45,400
Hey, young man!
You filling in for Dindin today?

163
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:47,359
Yes. I'm taking over for Dindin today.

164
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:49,480
Did he trick you into doing this?

165
00:11:50,040 --> 00:11:52,280
Not at all. I'm doing this willingly.

166
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:53,640
Alright then.

167
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:59,240
Koh Larn, this way! Koh Larn, over here!

168
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:13,720
Mr. Sailom,

169
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:18,680
I want to thank you for
coming back to see me.

170
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:21,800
You're welcome.

171
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:31,320
During our sessions, if there's
anything you'd like to share,

172
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:35,680
please tell me anything.
I'm here to listen.

173
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:39,880
Yes.

174
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:49,240
And everything we discuss today will be
kept confidential for your treatment only.

175
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:52,080
Do I have your permission?

176
00:12:57,800 --> 00:12:58,920
Yes, you do.

177
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:04,040
Thank you very much. So...

178
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:06,720
did you have anything
for breakfast this morning?

179
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:11,360
Not yet.

180
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:13,840
I didn't really have an appetite.

181
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:20,720
You didn't have breakfast
because you didn't feel like eating.

182
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:25,280
Is there any food you particularly like?

183
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:30,000
Well... fish steak.

184
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:32,280
Oh, fish steak.

185
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:37,880
What kind of fish? Dory or Salmon?

186
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,079
Salmon.

187
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:44,120
Oh! I love salmon too!

188
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:50,000
And do you usually
have it with any side dishes?

189
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:53,560
Like som tam, fries, or salad?

190
00:13:54,720 --> 00:14:01,160
Mashed potatoes, fries, and soup.

191
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,080
Sailom.

192
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:24,400
Where would you like to go today?

193
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,960
I'd rather go home.

194
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:32,880
Let's go to your place. To my car.

195
00:14:48,157 --> 00:14:49,483
Let me try!

196
00:14:49,697 --> 00:14:51,403
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, of course!

197
00:14:54,177 --> 00:14:55,016
Okay, then give it a try.

198
00:14:56,983 --> 00:14:59,857
Is this som tam noodles
or wide rice noodles?

199
00:15:00,238 --> 00:15:02,171
Like this, right?
The Luang Prabang style.

200
00:15:02,196 --> 00:15:03,363
Oh, then I’ll have
Luang Prabang style.

201
00:15:03,530 --> 00:15:04,537
Luang Prabang som tam?
Really?

202
00:15:04,914 --> 00:15:06,334
That's right! Now grab me chilli.

203
00:15:06,814 --> 00:15:08,447
The green one or red one?

204
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:30,400
They might not look
as fancy as restaurant dishes,

205
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:32,480
but I guarantee they're delicious.

206
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:38,160
I think they look and taste amazing

207
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:42,000
because you made me
do so much of the work.

208
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,040
But I seasoned it.

209
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:47,439
I watched a Japanese food show once.

210
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:52,920
They said the secret to
delicious food is all in the cutting.

211
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,199
Okay, I give up.

212
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,440
Do you know why?

213
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:59,600
- Why?
- Because I'm starving. Let's eat.

214
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:03,120
Here, try your own masterpiece first.

215
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:04,160
Here.

216
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:08,360
Ahh…

217
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:12,040
Nom.

218
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:16,320
Mmm!

219
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:17,560
What does “Mmm” mean?

220
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:20,040
- Good.
- Really?

221
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:22,120
It's a bit too spicy for you.

222
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:26,000
My turn. Let me try some.

223
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:29,479
One, two...

224
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:31,600
- Wow! This is so good!
- Not yet!

225
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:34,600
Ahh…

226
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:00,720
Hope your grandma can eat this.

227
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:06,600
Old man.

228
00:17:07,840 --> 00:17:09,520
Take your damn money back.

229
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,480
I never asked you to pay for
my grandma's medical bill.

230
00:17:15,080 --> 00:17:17,520
I already paid. Just keep it.

231
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:20,560
Do you think I can't afford the bill?!

232
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:26,480
That's not what I think.

233
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:29,920
I just don't want to see you struggling.

234
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,599
Struggling? What struggle?

235
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:33,880
I'm fine!

236
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:36,640
Just admit that you have money problems.

237
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:41,560
Why else would you be singing,
taking boat tickets, and making sweets?

238
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,360
That's my business!

239
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:45,040
Stay out of it!

240
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:47,000
Because you're my employee!

241
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:49,640
If you don't show up,

242
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:51,880
my shop has nothing to sell!

243
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:57,000
If you really want to pay me back,

244
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:59,440
I can deduct it from your salary.

245
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:04,120
(Dick.)

246
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:07,480
But you have to pay interest.

247
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:12,920
What interest?

248
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:15,440
Drink with me every night.

249
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,920
Just say you're horny.

250
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:24,600
Yeah, I'm horny.

251
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:10,640
Is camping with a boyfriend
on your bucket list too?

252
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:12,560
Yeah.

253
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:17,160
This trip is actually one of them.

254
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:25,040
I've wanted to go camping
with a boyfriend for so long,

255
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:28,360
but I never had a partner

256
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:30,600
and time.

257
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:33,440
About when you got fired...

258
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:38,240
After I found out I had cancer...

259
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:42,360
I didn't want to live anymore.

260
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:45,760
I just thought

261
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,840
I'd try everything I'd never done.

262
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:54,760
Like… drinking,

263
00:19:57,160 --> 00:19:58,560
hitting up host bars,

264
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:01,480
and having a boyfriend.

265
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,719
I wanted to live it up,

266
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:07,080
to make this life feel worth it.

267
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:11,080
Is there anything else you want to do?

268
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:17,560
Well...

269
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,440
I do.

270
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:22,280
There are places I want to go.

271
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:26,160
I spent all my time working
and never went anywhere.

272
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:32,600
Where… do you want to go?

273
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:38,040
I…

274
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:40,560
Want to travel abroad.

275
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:45,160
I've never even been to Japan.

276
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:48,280
Go…

277
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:50,280
see the London Eye,

278
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:53,120
try…

279
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:57,040
parachuting or skydiving,

280
00:20:57,800 --> 00:21:00,720
visit the Great Wall,

281
00:21:02,080 --> 00:21:06,320
Bali, Hawaii... so many places.

282
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:07,680
Mhm.

283
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:21,680
If that's what you want,

284
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:26,680
you need to get better first, okay?

285
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:30,360
Once you're better,

286
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:34,720
I'll take you everywhere you want to go.

287
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:37,200
I promise.

288
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:03,320
So... where should we go first?

289
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:04,840
I think…

290
00:22:06,320 --> 00:22:07,920
London sounds interesting.

291
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:10,480
I've always wanted
to see the London Eye too.

292
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:11,600
Really?

293
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:19,480
Why are you crying?

294
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:05,840
Nabnueng,

295
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:08,640
you already know this.

296
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:14,880
The best form of healing is
rebuilding trust in humanity.

297
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:20,240
Or making Sailom trust someone

298
00:23:20,280 --> 00:23:22,760
and learning to lean on those around him.

299
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,680
Sailom!

300
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:46,560
Are you ready?

301
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:47,600
Ready!

302
00:23:48,040 --> 00:23:49,200
Let's go then.

303
00:24:18,880 --> 00:24:22,000
Do you usually enjoy watching movies?

304
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:24,400
I love them.

305
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:25,760
How often do you watch them?

306
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,400
About once a week.

307
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,480
Wow! Once a week?

308
00:24:29,520 --> 00:24:32,760
That means you watch
four movies a month.

309
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:34,800
That's right.

310
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:38,360
Is there a particular
movie that you love?

311
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:43,200
I really like “First Love.”

312
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:49,280
Oh, so you're a fan of romantic movies?

313
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:51,440
I love that one too!

314
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:52,480
Really?

315
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:08,160
I'm going to let it go now.
Slow and steady.

316
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:10,680
- Like this?
- A bit more. Watch out for the string.

317
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:13,640
Do you feel that? Feel the wind?

318
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:14,720
Run.

319
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:24,120
How are you feeling today, Mr. Sailom?

320
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:27,279
I feel like...

321
00:26:27,280 --> 00:26:29,840
I can touch other people again.

322
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:32,000
Really?

323
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:37,039
I heard you did some activities
with your friends at the beach?

324
00:26:37,040 --> 00:26:38,080
Yes.

325
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:41,000
We played Monkey in the Middle

326
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:44,159
and flew kites together.

327
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:47,079
So, during Monkey in the Middle,

328
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:50,320
you could touch your friends?

329
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:00,520
Yes.

330
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:04,480
While we were chasing the ball,

331
00:27:04,520 --> 00:27:08,280
I was touching and bumping into others.

332
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:09,840
Yes.

333
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:10,960
In that case,

334
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,200
could you try touching my hand

335
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:15,760
like you did with your friends?

336
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:25,320
Like when you touched your friends.

337
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:27,680
Okay.

338
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:46,359
You've improved so much.

339
00:27:46,360 --> 00:27:49,680
Now, may I have your
permission to touch your arm?

340
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:54,200
Yes, you may.

341
00:28:12,120 --> 00:28:13,360
Well done!

342
00:28:13,520 --> 00:28:15,120
This is wonderful!

343
00:28:16,040 --> 00:28:17,360
I actually did it!

344
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,280
You were amazing!

345
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:48,880
Dindin.

346
00:28:50,560 --> 00:28:52,160
Come have a drink with me.

347
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:58,360
Your life must be so stressful.

348
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:00,880
I see you drink all day.

349
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:03,200
Mind your own business.

350
00:29:06,040 --> 00:29:07,240
Dindin,

351
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:09,200
are you gonna join me?

352
00:29:09,560 --> 00:29:12,560
Yeah, let me finish
checking the stock first.

353
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:38,520
What are you doing here?

354
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:42,440
Just checking if you're done yet.

355
00:29:49,080 --> 00:29:50,400
Be real with me.

356
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:53,160
You're horny?

357
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:58,880
Just let me finish this first.

358
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:30,760
Hey!

359
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:38,120
If you don't stop messing with me,

360
00:30:39,320 --> 00:30:41,560
you're gonna be eating my fist.

361
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:44,240
Going to punch me again?

362
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:48,560
Is it a tradition to throw
a punch before we kiss?

363
00:30:51,160 --> 00:30:54,960
Can we try kissing without
the punching for once?

364
00:30:58,120 --> 00:30:59,920
Don't want to have a sore lip.

365
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:07,920
Come on, put your clothes on.

366
00:32:08,800 --> 00:32:10,120
Why?

367
00:32:11,720 --> 00:32:12,760
Well...

368
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:16,520
we go our separate ways after we're done.

369
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:25,880
Can I stay like this for a little longer?

370
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:39,920
(Savings Account: 47,596.59 baht)

371
00:33:40,760 --> 00:33:43,600
I… want to travel abroad.

372
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:49,560
If that's what you want,

373
00:33:51,759 --> 00:33:55,119
you need to get better first, okay?

374
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:58,280
Once you're better,

375
00:33:59,320 --> 00:34:03,040
I'll take you everywhere you want to go.

376
00:34:30,240 --> 00:34:32,919
Nava. I got a lot of vegetables today.

377
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:34,960
I was thinking of making stir-fry…

378
00:34:37,680 --> 00:34:39,840
Nava? Where are you going?

379
00:34:40,600 --> 00:34:41,880
I want to go home.

380
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:44,160
Why?

381
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:46,240
Why so suddenly?

382
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:48,320
Is there something wrong at home?

383
00:34:50,193 --> 00:34:51,793
Everything's fine at home.

384
00:34:52,615 --> 00:34:54,495
I just want to go home to die.

385
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:55,800
Die?

386
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:58,360
I thought we talked about this.

387
00:34:58,720 --> 00:35:01,000
You were going to get treatment.

388
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:03,840
I don't think I ever said that.

389
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:06,360
You just assumed it yourself.

390
00:35:08,513 --> 00:35:09,633
Nava…

391
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:13,320
I'm asking you seriously.

392
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:20,080
Did you ever once love me?

393
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:24,400
Or am I just some host

394
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:27,080
you used for fun before you died?

395
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:32,560
I feel like I mean nothing to you.

396
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:38,240
You want to give up, you want to die.

397
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:39,960
You keep saying that!

398
00:35:41,480 --> 00:35:43,280
Have you ever thought…

399
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:46,160
about how I'll live...

400
00:35:47,040 --> 00:35:48,680
if you're gone?

401
00:35:53,640 --> 00:35:55,960
If you wanted to die from the start,

402
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:02,160
why did you make me love you?

403
00:36:08,760 --> 00:36:10,000
Sky...

404
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:12,040
I'm sorry.

405
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:16,360
I'm so sorry.

406
00:36:22,240 --> 00:36:23,920
I do love you, Sky.

407
00:36:26,880 --> 00:36:27,920
But...

408
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:30,040
I've run out of money.

409
00:36:32,520 --> 00:36:34,800
I can't afford the treatment anymore.

410
00:36:36,520 --> 00:36:38,400
I just can't.

411
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:43,800
I don't have the money.

412
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:17,400
Are you nervous?

413
00:37:18,533 --> 00:37:21,133
A little. But I'm more hungry.

414
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:25,920
Hang in there. You can eat
whatever you want after the surgery.

415
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:31,520
I'll take you everywhere,

416
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:33,800
and we'll do everything

417
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:36,280
on your list.

418
00:37:36,720 --> 00:37:37,880
Fight on.

419
00:37:44,240 --> 00:37:46,520
Is this a hospital or a maze?

420
00:37:46,560 --> 00:37:48,280
Took me forever to find this room.

421
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,240
I brought you some oranges.

422
00:37:50,440 --> 00:37:51,840
Man, it's you…

423
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:56,320
Hey, show some respect
to your “Major Sponsor,” will you?

424
00:37:57,240 --> 00:37:58,680
What sponsor?

425
00:38:00,733 --> 00:38:02,693
Haven't you told him yet?

426
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:24,440
Sky?

427
00:38:25,120 --> 00:38:26,440
P'Man,

428
00:38:27,413 --> 00:38:29,173
please help my boyfriend.

429
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:36,400
Sky never asked me for anything,

430
00:38:37,099 --> 00:38:38,939
unlike the other hosts.

431
00:38:39,613 --> 00:38:42,573
That's why I like him.

432
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:44,920
Thanks for telling me

433
00:38:44,960 --> 00:38:48,200
you like my boyfriend in front of me.

434
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:54,200
What does that have to do
with the money for my treatment?

435
00:38:55,040 --> 00:38:58,480
Has the cancer reached your brain?

436
00:38:58,560 --> 00:39:00,000
It's in my colon.

437
00:39:00,375 --> 00:39:01,855
Whatever.

438
00:39:02,227 --> 00:39:03,667
But use your head.

439
00:39:03,859 --> 00:39:06,099
Someone who
never asks for anything for himself,

440
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:09,360
but comes begging me
to save his boyfriend…

441
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:11,640
Think about how much he loves you.

442
00:39:12,280 --> 00:39:14,360
It hurts just talking about it.

443
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:24,640
Thank you so much, P'Man.

444
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:27,680
Huh? What did you call me?

445
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:29,560
P'Man.

446
00:39:34,799 --> 00:39:36,559
And I'm sorry

447
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:39,200
for everything in the past.

448
00:39:40,800 --> 00:39:42,240
Just get well soon

449
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:44,680
so you can work and pay me back.

450
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:48,920
Do you know how many
drinks this money could've bought?

451
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:51,800
Thank you.

452
00:39:52,600 --> 00:39:53,600
I'm going.

453
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:56,280
Oh, and don't worry.

454
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:58,840
I won't use this money
as an excuse to mess with Sky.

455
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:01,000
There are plenty of other hosts.

456
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:03,800
P'Man,

457
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,200
I thank you again.

458
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:10,200
Happy to help.

459
00:40:11,655 --> 00:40:13,535
P'Man, your hand…

460
00:40:13,866 --> 00:40:15,346
Just a little bit.

461
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:27,320
Thank you, Sky.

462
00:40:28,080 --> 00:40:29,680
For doing all of this for me.

463
00:40:30,480 --> 00:40:32,120
Don't thank me.

464
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:34,000
You don't have to.

465
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:38,040
Just get better and stay with me…

466
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:40,280
That's all I need.

467
00:42:11,680 --> 00:42:12,840
Sailom...

468
00:42:18,640 --> 00:42:20,840
Will you be my boyfriend?

469
00:42:32,487 --> 00:42:34,367
Is it going to be a burden

470
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:39,520
to be with a broken man like me?

471
00:42:46,960 --> 00:42:48,280
I don't know.

472
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:51,520
We'll have to find out.

473
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:04,200
In that case...

474
00:43:07,720 --> 00:43:09,320
do we try kissing?

475
00:44:50,200 --> 00:44:51,376
(Next Episode)
Are you really cured?

476
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:55,960
Cured or not, but the doctor
asked me to be his boyfriend!

477
00:44:59,080 --> 00:45:00,720
The boss sent me to collect the interest.

478
00:45:01,360 --> 00:45:04,280
I'll do whatever
it takes to keep this house.

479
00:45:05,200 --> 00:45:08,640
My mother told me to help
my sick biological sister.

480
00:45:08,680 --> 00:45:11,080
- How?
- A bone marrow transplant.

481
00:45:11,200 --> 00:45:13,760
It has to come from a full
sibling with the same parents.

482
00:45:14,280 --> 00:45:15,160
Have you seen your sister?

483
00:45:15,240 --> 00:45:17,200
I just saw her taking out the trash.

484
00:45:17,480 --> 00:45:18,760
Who the hell are these bastards?

